responses.title: Existence as you perceive it is but a shade of the infinite realm.
Long have my celestial brothers beckoned...
I am the void and the spirit.
I abhor the blindness of the mortal plane.
I step again into the mortal plane.
Before me, the map of all of time unfolds...
It is time for the celestials to unite...or fall before me.
This path leads amongst my brothers, where they have long wished I'd go.
The great confluence approaches and my time finally comes.
Friend or foe, in the wake of the confluence, you will follow where I lead.
I step from the void's embrace.
Long have my celestial brothers beckoned...
I am the void and the spirit.
I abhor the blindness of the mortal plane.
We will test ourselves in battle to prepare for the war to come.
I step again into the mortal plane.
Your comprehension is not required. Only your cooperation.
The passage of time on the mortal plane is immensely...tedious.
Existence as you perceive it is but a shade of the infinite realm.
Before me, the map of all of time unfolds...
It is time for the celestials to unite...or fall before me.
This path leads amongst my brothers, where they have long wished I'd go.
I tip the balance of the cosmic scale.
I step from my Hidden Temple.
Those who have served me will at last know my true face.
My sight's horizon nears its end...
I visit these lands sparingly, but to great effect.
I will not allow the Hidden Temple to fall.
A dark energy... but not a dark intent.
The great confluence approaches and my time finally comes.
Those who serve me seek wisdom, not reward.
Always I will choose one. At times, I may choose many.
We must ready this plane to face the threats to come.
There is no inherent meaning to your mortal lives. That, you must leave to those of us above.
I suffer the indignities of the mortal plane only so long as I must.
My path leads where few can follow.
I arrive to avert the destruction that comes.
Embrace the infinite possibilities of the void.
Friend or foe, in the wake of the confluence, you will follow where I lead.
The path of this conflict was decided long ago.
I do not concern myself with the bag, for I know its contents well.
The map of all of time unfolds before me...In lines that streak across the astral plane.
A single mistep could undo aeons of planning. Even I must be careful.
I was always watching. Now I lend a hand.
Everything is in place. Only one task remains.
Now I lay their plans to waste.
Now my plans will lay their plans to waste.
Do I choose this path or does it choose me?
Do you think I've not seen this?
Do I choose this path or does it choose me?
Do you think I've not seen this?
There is no flight from me.
There is no flight from me.
I will always watch over me.
I am all of the Hidden Ones.
Secret paths known only to me.
Anywhere you can go, I can be waiting.
The hidden path reveals your demise.
Wherever you go, there I am.
This is why they call me the Hidden ONES.
It isn't shadow that bathes me.
I do not like to be touched.
Huh huh he he he he.
Huh ha ha ha ha ha ha.
I appear in my proper place.
I must admit to enjoying that.
I must bring the full measure of my power into this realm.
Soon my powers may well be enough...
None see the threat that looms.
A brimful of aether will help my side.
Only I can draw upon the strength of the void.
The power of the void breaks across the planes.
Hn hn ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha haa.
Hn hn hn ha ha ha ha ha ha ha haa.
Ah! Ha ha ha ha ha ha haa!
Your time and place have come and gone.
You were placed on my path for this reason.
Each moment of your life led without doubt... to this.
Your final gasp serves as bellows to the whirlwinds of destruction.
Your fate line was unfortunate to touch my path.
The entirety of your existence was but a single moment.
Rest well. Your death has consequence.
Who cannot maintain will always fall.
The void minds not your existence, for the void minds not.
Your life served no purpose, but your death may still.
I push the future ever further towards my own ends.
Your life was a flash in the blink of my eye.
You sought to bargain something of little value.
Why did you make an enemy of me? I had no reason to notice you...
You could merely hope to amount even to nothing.
You cannot escape that which is all around you.
You haven't failed. This was your greatest success.
There is nothing for you here. There is nothing for you anywhere.
I must forgive you for being only what you are.
You seem to have trouble grasping cause and effect.
You must learn to live with the void inside.
Surrender all hope to the void.
If you look long enough into the void...
There is nothing outside the void.
The wisdom of eternity guides my blade.
Hm hm hm hm hm hm hm hm hm hm.
Mm hm hm hm hm hm hmm hm hm hmm hm hm hm hm hm.
Hm hm hm ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha haa.
Hm ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha haa.
Even a god is nothing set against the void.
You never understood--or even truly questioned--why you were given this power.
Nothing you could conjure in the material plane would have been enough to save you.
The Turstarkuri were consumed by their own folly. They let themselves be slaughtered.
Your masters misunderstood my teachings. But their folly ends with you.
I felt the ripples of your birth. The consequences will end not with your death.
If your greatest ambition was to ride a bat, you die not a failure.
Is there a discernable difference between your kind and those you call beasts?
You concern yourself only with gluttony. And this is where that path leads.
You see little of the path for one so concerned with tracks.
Once you would have been a powerful ally...
A life of constant battle can only end like this.
Armageddon has lost a step or two...
I expected this. I never thought to find an ally in one such as you.
You sought to control the world around you. Yet each choice led to here.
Your curse is nothing to the void.
You donned the armor. You met your end.
For a mortal to possess such power is...quaint.
I could have shown you a way beyond the wall...
You come from a race of insects. Easily swatted.
You have wasted gifts untold, crone.
Mortals fear you. I do not.
I honor the power of the elder inside you.
You find your true tribe amongst the dead.
Tethered to this plane, you accomplish nothing.
I could have been powerful friend to you, Earthshaker.
The creator falls like all the rest.
Did you think I was one of your creations?
I alone see the way forward.
What is a flame burning in the void?
Your actions endanger that which you swore to protect.
We could have accomplished much as allies, Enigma.
This will play havoc with the universe...
You understand the dangers that lie ahead and yet you stand against me?
Sailing upon the ocean is not the same as swimming in the sea.
A petulant pursuit for power meets its proper end.
Your inventions hardly lift you above the rabble.
You cannot escape me, Io. Our paths are linked.
There would be no arcane arts without the void.
I had hoped the wisdom of your kind would help you choose a better path.
It brings me no pleasure to extinguish the first light.
The sea is a storm pond when compared to the void.
A better death than at the hands of a demon.
What other end could one such as you meet?
You certainly were a presumptuous child.
Your tormented existence comes to a merciful end.
The soul of the slayer has been enveloped by the void.
Your timeless history is a footnote in the scheme of the universe.
You'd have wasted another span of years anyway.
Your goddess doesn't care to help you, child. Not that she could.
Noble creatures die the same as the wretched.
What does the word god mean to me, pup?
There will be no justice for you.
Your titles mean nothing to me.
Gods never fared well against you, but I am not a god.
You were of great interest to me, Morphling. Perhaps in another life...
There's no one to hear you sing in the void.
Such a limited imagination you have.
You must learn to respect your elders.
Your talents could have been leveraged for so much more...
The goddess of luck always was a moron.
Would you like to know what the Omniscience is, Purist? Hm hm hm hm.
It isn't prophecy so much as foresight and an excellent vantage.
You fought well for a rolling ball of meat.
You would not have done well in my service. I seek out a different kind.
This does not please me, youngling.
Without decay...your life truly ends here.
I warned you not to interrupt me.
Demons. Creatures of great power and limited intelligence.
I've broken your loop, Razor. Let it not start again.
I once thought a mortal unseen would be the most pleasant kind. I was mistaken.
A great lineage comes to a nullifying end.
Such regional concerns are beneath my time.
I don't waste my time with petty criminals.
Your singular focus blinds you to the real matters at hand.
Your magics were surprisingly powerful, but your case was hopeless all the same.
You know nothing of silence, boy.
Your new Queen won't even mourn you.
Your depths aren't nearly as black as the void.
You were not long for this world anyway. But it is a shame about that wonderful dragon-toad.
This is as kind a death as you could hope for, small one. Others would do much worse.
This is a merciful end to your ceaseless wandering.
Will your master show himself, or must I seek him out again?
I was the first of us, and I shall be the last.
You would have the same chance wielding a sharp stick.
You pose a danger only to those who are tethered to the earth.
After all that has been given... Still you cannot rise above your mortal ways.
The temple casts you out. I shall find another.
That you were kept prisoner at all proves you were unworthy.
Your god will need to find a new plaything...
The mortal mind is so easily brought to ruin.
I would have called you ally, Tiny.
Your bravery is noted. It's meaningless of course, but I will remember.
I can go anywhere, yet have invaded nowhere. Expand your ambitions.
Your kind is lost on a grim charade.
You had no cause to die here.
Was it not vengeance you desired? You chose the wrong path.
You're larger than but somehow still less than a worm.
You still wouldn't have had a chance had you learned proper magics, but it would have been closer.
My affairs do not concern you.
Such ingenuity from such an insignificant brain.
It isn't possible to weave a fate untouched by the void.
I suspect some elemental loyalty may have been misplaced.
You had the power and the intellect, yet let it come to waste.
Your quaint magics were at least amusing to the eye.
Your thirst for life amounts to nothing in the end.
It would have been unlike you to start making good choices now.
Too ruled by fear and emotion to choose the winning side.
I'll recall you as a minor inconvenience. Which is one step up from a pest.
You were true to your purpose, I cannot deny.
I once thought you might aid my cause in a much greater capacity than fodder.
You thought you understood the true nature of this conflict. Fool.
Your trail of victims means nothing to me, Axe. YOU mean nothing to me.
Your potential has been dulled to the point of nothingness.
I was surprised you could even comprehend my existence.
Destroyed by the webs you yourself wove.
The powers of the Nothl realm are no secret to me.
The elements cannot hope to rein me in.
To deny my wisdom is to choose death.
From my perspective, you met this fate only moments after the rest of your kind.
You can't even grasp the true power of what you were given.
The fall of the last guardian and no one left to recognize its import.
The works of your life amount to nothing.
First blood. By an arbitrary definition.
First blood. Now to finish how it began.
First blood. The first celestial reigns.
Your ancestors made... interesting choices, Abbadon.
Your talents are applied to such unworthy ends, Razzil.
Have you knowledge of events to come, Kaldr?
Some secrets lead only to ruin, Anti-Mage.
Your watch soon comes to an end, Warden.
Each swing of your blade has been foretold, Axe.
What can you tell me of fear, Bane?
I've never had a nightmare. Only visions.
Place our cause before your gods of gluttony, Bloodseeker.
You are welcome to our cause, cousin, but no drinking spirits in the temple.
You sense it too, yes, cousin?
If you stopped chasing, perhaps he'd stop running, Chaos Knight.
You would be adrift without your ancient pursuit, Chaos Knight.
You're new to eternity, Clinkz. It gets better.
Your life need not end trapped on this rock, Dark Seer.
Why do you seek the Shadowgate Amulet, Mireska? I expect the toll of its use will not agree with you.
Your father spends his wealth in search of my temple. But such a path offers no purchase.
Come, brother. There's much to be done.
Your knowledge of this place will prove most helpful.
I have the answers you seek, Earthshaker. Come to me when the battle is over.
An eternity hasn't done any favors to your mood...
The moment is at hand, brother. There's much to be done.
We are not always in agreement, but we can at least work in alignment.
I don't judge your hobbies, Enigma. Who am I to say what's abnormal?
I watched the evolution of your kind with great curiosity, Darkterror.
You have come by a power few mortals will ever know. I wonder if it's wasted on you...
I hardly remember a time before you, Io.
This battle can hardly start without the pair of us, Io.
I'm impressed that you've not only heard of the Korumite, but you even remember some incantations.
Before I even knew myself, I felt your headlong flight.
I've enjoyed watching your journey, Ezalor.
Yes, that's one way to look at the universe, Leshrac, but I'd argue it's a bit of a stretch.
Demons? You set your sights pretty low, Lion.
Your goddess vouches for you, so I'll acknowledge your presence.
I don't mind your self-indulgence, Mars, just so long as you keep swinging that spear.
The concept of royalty is rather amusing. As are humans in general. At least a queen bee serves a biological purpose.
You've provided much amusement, Wu Kong. It's always entertaining to see divine arrogance brought low.
I serve no gods, Wukong. I merely had later need of you and this version is much more useful.
Your tastes are timeless, Night Stalker... I expect you'll never change.
You could serve my interests well, Nyx... Should you choose to do so.
I have not gleaned what comes beyond this battle, Oracle. Is your sight the same?
Does the old road go unguarded?
The high road may be lost to you Assassin, but there are other paths to follow...
Some of the first visitors to my temple were ancestors of yours.
None of it truly matters, Skywrath. Try to let it go.
Amusing that they call you an outlander...
We couldn't be more different, yet we're inextricably linked...
I warned you to follow my instructions to the letter...
I make no apologies for allowing Thunderkeg to stumble upon that forbidden spell.
Try to contain that wild streak for once and stick to the plan.
You have done well, child. Now your true service comes to pass.
You do not recognize me, Lanaya. But I am known to you all the same.
In some ways, you're more alive than most mortals will ever be.
Zeus, I must say your attraction to mortals is...puzzling.
The best you could hope for.
I take no pleasure in culling a lesser foe.
The best you could hope for.
I take no pleasure in culling a lesser foe.
This one was not for you.
Did you think it was yours?
I see a lot of nothing in your future.
This one was not for you.
Did you think it was yours?
I see a lot of nothing in your future.
What would you have me give?
Blood coin pays passage in this land.
If my enemies had hope before, none remains.
I must admit, occasionally a mortal DOES create something of consequence...
It was wise to share this recipe.
They will weep as the void takes them.
I could drink this all day.
This is not the first time I've felt the heft of this blade.
Only this can contain the void.
This will complement my skills nicely.
I always knew where to find you, Kaya. It simply wasn't time.
The truth of sight is always welcome.
This is a strange land, to be sure.
Hm! And mortals underestimate its power...
This is ... the path I must walk.
Ages of preparation... come to this...
I fear not ... the journey ahead.
True power ... attracts its own kind.
This couldn't have happened...in the void.
The meaning you ascribe to this...is false.
When next you turn around...I will be there.
You cannot truly pierce the void...
You do not see the true danger...
I step from the void's embrace.
There's nothing out there but the void.
My work here is not yet done.
Before there was something... there was nothing.
I must endure the indignities of the mortal coil...
Was this part of my plan, you ask? All that occurs is well accounted for.
I stay true to the course.
The universe reminds me of my place.
Even my plans are a just toss in the dark...
The enemy is more formidable than I'd thought.
This plane does not suit me, but the work is not yet done.
Emotion is like any other tool -- easily mishandled.
Perhaps I was hidden for too long...
I have reformed myself from the fabric of the void.
Now to plan the proper application...
I restore my connection to the void.
Before there was the spirit, there was the void. Before there was anything, there was the void.
Long after -- though only a moment in the scope of the whole -- there came...a being of great power.
Still without comprehensible form or voice of my own, I felt this titan's hammer fall and the four children scatter.
I began to find myself in the reverberations of the blow. And I saw the expanse of time flash forth from the instant.
In that cascade of moments, I knew I must learn to compose a form capable of interacting with the material plane.
Those who see little think this battle to be the end of things.
For some, it may be. For others, the fall of an Ancient signals a fight of a different kind.
I sense distortions in the void.
Something comes. And none alone can stop it.
I have taken a form more able to interact with the matters of the mortal plane, but I do not pass my time here.
To house this body and the artifacts it collects, I long ago constructed a hidden bastion.
A temple fashioned after a Korumite design -- far removed from the reach of all but those very few I permit to chance across it.
Many do my bidding, but none know my true face.
Some amongst them are privy to a degree of wisdom, while others remain blind.
I have seen everything just beyond this moment. But there soon comes a point where I am blind.
I do not worry. I have made every preparation for what I imagine lies ahead.
I do not enjoy how it feels to walk the mortal plane, but mortals themselves can be quite amusing.
The decisions they make are nothing but astounding. But how can they choose otherwise? They cannot truly see.
I do not stop their scurrying if I can help it. And if they get in my way...their deaths will not be unkind.
The Temple of the Korumite monks was filled with scholars wise enough to study both the martial and arcane arts, yet humble enough to know they did not possess the wisdom to correctly wield them.
Very few mortals since have earned my respect like the Korumite. That barely a single soul remembers them is no small reason why.
Soon the fabric of this realm will merge with others, and the ripples of destruction will touch all planes equally.
There could be no arcane art were it not for the void. While not the sole ingredient, it is certainly a vital one.
You have the gratitude of the void.
Thank you. I shall reconsider your worth.
This pleases me to no end.

Celebrate for a few moments, but prepare yourselves for the chaos to come.
Contain yourself. This was the expected outcome.

I did not ask for it, but I welcome it.

What good is your sight when you lack comprehension?
The void is not absence. The void is omnipresence!
How can you carry hope in the face of the void?
I will not harm those who do not stand in my way.
